            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk @linkarzu I have an unfinished branch that does a few things:\n\n1. It switches absolute image placement to instead be only within neovim by using floating windows with unicode. I don't know if we need this, but was flagged a long time ago that since we're using the terminal coordinate space, some terminals that have splits don't properly adjust and therefore if you had say a vertical split with neovim on the right, any of your image positions at row 1, col 1 would show up outside of neovim on the left split. When I tried in ghostty, it didn't have that problem, but maybe other terminals it does.\n2. It supports injecting images into buffers using unicode. Seems to work decently well from what I've seen. I just followed what you had expressed for this issue since I'd tried before with actual text reflow and it was a nightmare.\n\nThe code is pretty ugly, so going to need a little time to clean it up, but I'll send it your way in a couple of days as a prototype to see how it might work in the future, @justinmk \n\nVideo shows image moving around in a buffer, image showing up when you have multiple windows for the same buffer, image disappearing when you delete the line with the image, image making room for itself to fit in the buffer, and absolute positioning still working but now relative to the neovim editor instead of all of a terminal.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1539d5fb-11b8-4e11-ad4d-cc693be407fc",
